metadata.name: The Age of Automata #81
metadata.description:
This is an exploration of cellular automaton to find simplicity and beauty in mathematics.

First, a grid with random dimensions is created. A color palette is randomly selected from a large number of palettes, and a cellular automaton is formed based on one of the rules, and this operation may be repeated randomly to form a relatively more complex pattern. Finally, a number of geometries are combined with the automaton to make the mint harmonious and unique.

The idea was inspired by discoveries of Wolfram and Ciphrd’s artwork. 

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

I recently launched my Twitter, so if you have any questions and would like to know about my next work or have a suggestion, you can contact me through this account:

https://twitter.com/_XSaha

Made with P5js.

metadata.name: Just, Steven! #1
metadata.description:
Just,Steven - is a shell that has always followed me, or has been a part of me, I never fully understood. This is a character who ironically, because of the many social culture shifts in his life, began to resort to the way of putting other people's faces and stories on himself. At first it was necessary to adapt in a certain circle of society so as not to be a black sheep, after a few years he stopped noticing how the consciousness itself uses the stories or phrases he has already heard from absolutely different people received during a conversation, news or other, another of the features is the numerous personalities of Steven.

I am creating this project because I have long wanted to try to tell people that being yourself is the most difficult and wonderful feeling. My goal is to get an animated movie adaptation on Netflix, the script will be written by anyone who wants to participate in the community. 

Peace be with you all!

Millefoglie #307
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ​[mil fœj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Carême.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (pâte feuilletée), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (crème pâtissière). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." — Wikipedia
